        <li>Submit misleading, fraudulent, or deceptive ad content</li>
        <li>Artificially inflate impressions, clicks, or other event metrics</li>
        <li>Attempt to manipulate auction outcomes or reverse-engineer bidding algorithms</li>
        <li>Use the Service to distribute malware or harmful content</li>
        <li>Violate any applicable laws or regulations in connection with your use of the Service</li>
        <li>Exceed rate limits or abuse the API in a manner that degrades service for others</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">5. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        The Service, including its software, design, and documentation, is owned by VectorSpace Exchange. Advertisers retain ownership of their ad creatives and content. Publishers retain ownership of their applications. Each party grants the other a limited license to use their content solely for the purpose of operating the ad exchange.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">6. Payment terms</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Advertisers are billed based on VCG auction prices for delivered impressions and clicks. Publishers receive revenue share payments as specified in their publisher agreement. Payment terms, schedules, and thresholds are detailed in the applicable publisher or advertiser agreement.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">7. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        The Service is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. To the maximum extent permitted by law, VectorSpace Exchange shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenue, whether incurred directly or indirectly. Our total liability for any claim arising from these Terms or the Service shall not exceed the amounts paid by or to you in the twelve months preceding the claim.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">8. Termination</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Either party may terminate their use of the Service at any time. We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms or engage in fraudulent activity. Upon termination, outstanding payment obligations survive.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">9. Governing law</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any disputes arising from these Terms shall be resolved in the state or federal courts located in San Francisco County, California.
